what is a function declaration?
 A function declaration tells the compiler about a function's name, return type, and parameters.

what is a return type and function parameters?
The return_type is the data type of the value the function returns.
what does the above statement mean?

return_type function_name( parameter list ) {
   body of the function
}-what does it mean? 
   -it gives the information about the type of function i.e., add or max etc and the parameters are like the input 
which you give to the particular function to take like a,b or some variable which will be able to take the values to operate that function
int max(int num1, int num2);this might be the possible example for the the above statement.In this statement integer is the return type , 
max is the function name and int num1 and int num2 are the parameters.

